Call me Darth Balls. Bunngg.
Jay leaps at Cock-Knocker, wielding the double-beamed Bong
Saber.
CHAKA
(from behind the
monitor)
I think George Lucas is going to sue
somebody--
EXT. SOUNDSTAGE--DAY
Willenholly's car screeches up, and Willenholly jumps with a
shotgun. He slides across the hood of the car and lands beside
the flashing red light.
WILLENHOLLY
(looking around)
So, this is Hollywood?
(suddenly full of
purpose)
Lights, camera, action, Jay and Silent
Bob.
Willenholly cocks his shotgun and heads for the door.
INT. SOUNDSTAGE--DAY
The door bursts open, and Willenholly charges in, firing two
shots, O.C.
WILLENHOLLY
FREEZE YOU TERRORIST SONSABITCHES!!!
Willenholly goes wide-eyed.
It's not Bluntcave. We're on a different soundstage, where a
kid's movie's being shot: Mooby's Grand Adventure. There's a
Barney-sized MOOBY surrounded by little KIDS. The Kids stare
back at Willenholly terrified. The Mooby suit has smoking
bullet holes in it. Mooby collapses.
WILLENHOLLY
Oh my God--
(to kids)
Um--sorry. That was supposed to be a
warning shot. Uh--it looks like I'm
on the wrong, uh--wrong set.
The Kids look at the fallen Mooby. On looks angrily at the
O.C. Willenholly.
KID
You killed Mooby--
(to Kids)
LET'S GET HIM!!!
The Kids charge Willenholly, who screams like a woman as
he's attacked.
INT. SOUNDSTAGE--SAME
Jay attacks Cock-Knocker with his Bong Saber, full throttle.
COCK-KNOCKER
(breaking character)
You are not upstaging me, Van Der
Beek!
Jay whacks away happily at the actor playing Cock-Knocker,
hacking him up onto the ladder of the Bluntcave's nuclear
reactor. Cock-Knocker climbs the ladder slightly to evade
the attack, dueling Jay back with the saber in his other
hand.
COCK-KNOCKER
(to O.C. Chaka)
CHAKA--CALL OFF DAWSON! GIVE ME A
"CUT"!
On cue, Jay delivers a kill-shot to one of Cock-Knocker's
huge fists, cutting it off (a la Empire).
Silent Bob joins Jay, as Jay turns off this double-Bong Saber,
Jay grins at Cock-Knocker.
JAY
Now whose balls have been busted,
bitch?
Suddenly, a gun shot rings out.
All turn to see a roughed-up Willenholly, training his gun
first on Jay, then Bob.
WILLENHOLLY
The C.L.I.T. stops here, Jay and
Silent Bob!
(revealing badge:
calling out)
Everyone stay calm. I'm a Federal
Wildlife Marshal. These men are the
leaders of a terrorist organization
wanted for the abduction of a monkey.
VOICE (O.S.)
They didn't really steal that monkey.
All turn to see Justice approaching from the shadows.
Willenholly trains his gun on her. Jay's mouth drops.
JUSTICE
It was just a diversion so we could
steal these.
Justice pulls the bag of diamonds from her jacket, revealing
them.
JUSTICE
And they're not the leaders of
C.L.I.T. The C.L.I.T. is not real.
WILLENHOLLY
No--the clit's real. The female orgasm
is a myth.
JUSTICE
(to Jay)
Are you guys alright?
JAY
I thought you blew up, Boo Boo Kitty
Fuck.
JUSTICE
(smiling)
You remembered.
(back to business)
It was a frame-up, Jay. Sissy. Missy,
Chrissy, and I are international
jewel thieves. We were setting you
up as a patsy, but I couldn't go
through with it, because I... because
I love you.
JAY
Yeah? So that means you'll fuck me,
right?
VOICE (O.S.)
If she does, it'll be considered
necrophilia.
All turn to see Sissy, Missy, and Chrissy slinking from the
shadows, guns drawn.
SISSY
Because she's gonna be one dead bitch.
(to Justice)
Hi, Jussy. We catch you at a bad
time?
MISSY
You should've just let these guys go
down, Jussy.
JAY
Hey, I wanted to go down, but I was
waiting until I got to know her a
little better. See, there was this
little angel on my shoulder, and he
said--
CHRISSY
Shut the fuck up before I shoot you
where you stand in your pansy red
booties.
JAY
(looking down)
Holy shit, I am wearing pansy red
booties!
(to Bob)
Man--why the fuck didn't you tell
me?
SISSY
Let's have those diamonds, Jussy.
JUSTICE
I can't do that, Sissy
SISSY
(points her gun at
Jay)
Then lover--boy gets one in the brain.
CHAKA
YO!
All turn to look at Chaka.
CHAKA
Would any of you lovely ladies like
a private audition to be in my movie?
Justice high-kicks the gun out of Sissy's hand. It lands on
the ground discharging. Then everyone starts shooting and
running for cover.
Jay and Silent Bob hurl themselves over the Bluntmobile.
Missy and Chrissy flip over a lavish, exquisitely-packed
craft service table labeled. CAST. They pop back up and start
firing at Willenholly. Willenholly leaps behind a barren
craft service table that holds a bag of Smarties and a dented
can of RC Cola. He pops up and returns fire. When both are
out of bullets, they drop back down behind the table and
reload. From behind his table,
Willenholly yells--
WILLENHOLLY
WHY ARE YOU SHOOTING AT ME?!?! I'M
JUST A FEDERAL WILDLIFE MARSHAL!!!
CHRISSY
TWO REASONS: ONE--WE'RE WALKING,
TALKING BAD GIRLS, CLICHES!
MISSY
AND TWO: BECAUSE YOU'RE A MAN.
WILLENHOLLY
ONLY ON THE OUTSIDE!
The Girls and Willenholly both pop back up and open fire
again.
Chaka ducks behind the monitor.
CHAKA
A shitload of white people with guns?
Time to get my black ass out of here!
He races off, passing Justice and Sissy, who circle each
other defensively, striking kung fu poses.
SISSY
You really let me down, Justice.
Throwing it all away for a little
stoner with bad pronunciation.
JAY (O.S.)
HEY!
JUSTICE
(ignoring him)
What's it gonna be, Sissy? Which
fighting style do you want me to
kick your ass in?
SISSY
Are you kidding me? I taught you all
all your moves myself. There's not a
style you can bust that I can't defend
against.
JUSTICE
You're no match for my "Shaolin Monk."
SISSY
Yeah, but I can bury you with my
"Crouching Tiger."
JUSTICE
A little "Venus's--flytrap"?
SISSY
I'll counter with "Dragon Crane."
JUSTICE
How about a little "Bitch, My Man
Ain't Yo Baby's Daddy"?
SISSY
(beat; smiles)
Bring it on.
Justice rushes Sissy and instead of sleek kung fu, they launch
into a down-and-dirty, girl's cat-fight; hair pulling and
screaming.
Behind the Bluntmobile, Jay and Bob watch all the action.
JAY
Yo--I hope one of 'em rips the other
one's shirt off and we see some tit.
Both Bob and Jay smile at each other, nodding. Banky joins
them, crawling in on his belly, covering his head.
BANKY
Mister Biggs? Mister Van Der Beek? I
just wanted to say hi. I'm--
JAY
Banky fucking Edwards! Just the
motherfucker we came to see!
BANKY
(shocked)
Holy shit! What the fuck are you
guys doing here?!
Sissy has Justice on her belly, banging her face into the
floor, screeching.  Jay, Bob, and Banky continue.
BANKY
Stop the movie?! Are you crazy?!
JAY
All these assholes are calling us
names on the Internet, 'cause of
this stupid movie!
BANKY
I feel for you boys--I really do.
Those Net snipers can be really cruel.
But Miramax paid me a shitload of
money for Bluntman and Chronic, so
it occurs to me that people bad-
mouthing you on some web-site is
none of my FUCKING CONCERN!
SILENT BOB
Oh--but I think it is.
Banky stares at Silent Bob, agog, Jay rolls his eyes.
JAY
Here we go again--
SILENT BOB
Shut the fuck up.
(to Banky)
We had a deal with you on the comics
for likeness rights. And as we're
not only the artistic basis but also
the character basis for your
intellectual property, Bluntman and
Chronic, when we said property was
optioned by Miramax Films you were
legally obliged to secure our
permission to transfer the concept
to another medium. As you failed to
do that, you're in breach of the
original contract--ergo, you find
yourself in a very actionable
position.
Banky stares at Bob, even more agog, joined by Jay. After a
beat, Jay adds--
JAY
Yeah.
Justice now has the advantage over Sissy, holding her head
and kicking her in the face, repeatedly, screaming.
BANKY
So, what do you guys want, to go
away and take your lady friends with
you?
JAY
Shitcan this movie so we don't get
called names on the Internet anymore.
BANKY
Even if there's no movie, people are
still free to talk shit about you on
the Internet. That's what the
Internet's for: slandering others
anonymously.  Stopping the flick
isn't going to stop that!
In the background, we see Justice high-kick Sissy into the
air.
JAY
Well this isn't fair!  We went to
Hollywood, I fell in love, we stole
a monkey, we got shot at, and got
punched in the motherfucking nuts!
We ain't leaving empty-handed!
On cue, Sissy drops from above, landing in Jay's lap.
JAY
What's up baby? You look good!
BANKY
Isn't that your girlfriend's enemy?
JAY
Oh yeah.
(pushing Sissy off
him)
Get the fuck offa me, pig!
Sissy races at Justice, leaping atop her, pulling her hair.
Jay, Bob, and Banky continue.
BANKY
You guys are gonna ruin my movie
career.
JAY
Well, we want something for our mental
anguish.
BANKY
Tell you what: we'll settle this
monetarily. I'll give you half of
what I made.
JAY
Half?!?
BANKY
Half's not good enough?  Fine--I'll
give you two-thirds of what I made!
JAY
Fuck-you--you already said half? You
can't take it back!
Silent Bob rolls his eyes, Banky shakes Jay's hand.
BANKY
Done
Justice throws Sissy off, onto the floor. Both get up, facing
each other.
SISSY
Your shit is so tired, Justice!
JUSTICE
Call me Boo-Boo Kitty Fuck--BITCH!
Justice high-kicks Sissy and she goes flying across the stage.
Sissy sails toward the craft service table, landing atop
Missy and Chrissy, knocking them out.
Willenholly stands to see why the girls stopped shooting.
WILLENHOLLY
Hello? Truce?
(beat)
I think I killed both of them.
Suddenly, he lets out a shriek and falls forward, revealing
a tranquilizer dart in his ass, and SUZANNE standing behind
him, holding the gun up in the air.  Justice surveys her
handiwork for a beat, then calls off toward the Bluntmobile.
JUSTICE
C'mon guys. It's over.
Jay, Bob, and Banky pop up from behind the car and join her.
JAY
Yo, I was just about to jump in there
and get your back.
Then, the SOUND of SIRENS rings out in the distance.
JAY
Holy shit, the cops! We gotta get
out of here!
JUSTICE
No. I'm tired of running.
Justice lifts Willenholly into a sitting position and taps
his face.
JUSTICE
You awake, Marshal? Marshal?
WILLENHOLLY
(tries to move but
can't)
Oh my God, I'm paralyzed. The monkey
shot me in the ass and paralyzed me!
Oh the irony!
JUSTICE
(off Suzanne's gun)
You're not paralyzed. It was just a
tranquilizer.
WILLENHOLLY
Jesus! Tranqued by a little monkey!
My friends in the Bureau are never
gonna let me live this down!
JUSTICE
You have friends in the F.B.I.?
WILLENHOLLY
(crying)
They all made it in, but I failed
the exam. Why the hell else do you
think I became a Federal Wildlife
Marshal? 'Cause I'm a joke!
Justice looks toward the direction of the sirens, thinking.
Then--
JUSTICE
Maybe not. I can make you a deal
that'll get you into the F.B.I.,
regardless of test scores.
WILLENHOLLY
What kind of deal?
JUSTICE
You drop the charges against Jay and
Silent Bob and say you never found
the ape.  Make sure the world knows
they're not in control of any C.L.I.T.
JAY
Now wait a second--
JUSTICE
I'll explain later, Jay
(to Willenholly)
In exchange, I'll give you the
diamonds I stole, and turn in Sissy,
Missy, Chrissy, and myself. But I
want a reduced sentence.
WILLENHOLLY
You'd be willing to do that?
JUSTICE
(off Jay)
For him? I'd be willing to do
anything.
Justice stands and takes Jay by the hands.
JUSTICE
I'm an international jewel thief
who's facing a jail sentence.
JAY
That's alright. I'm a junkie with a
monkey.
JUSTICE
If I go to prison, will you wait for
me?
JAY
I don't know. Will we fuck when you
get out?
Justice smiles and kisses Jay Passionately. The kiss should
say it all, but--
JAY
Don't change the subject. Will we
fuck when you get out?
JUSTICE
Snoogans.
Justice and Jay kiss again.
Suzanne reached up to Silent Bob, who picks her up. She grabs
his face and kisses him.
Willenholly looks to Banky.
WILLENHOLLY
Wow. There's a lot of love in the
room.
BANKY
Regardless of what you may have heard.
I do not kiss guys.
EXT. SOUNDSTAGE--LATER
Justice and Jay are still kissing, until Willenholly pulls
her away and loads her into the waiting Cop Car.
WILLENHOLLY
Sorry, Justice. We've gotta go.
(to Jay: friendly)
Hey--stop stealing monkeys.
JAY
Fuck you.
WILLENHOLLY
Fair enough.
Willenholly closes the door behind Justice and gets in the
car.
JUSTICE
(to Jay)
Wait for me.
JAY
What--here?
Jay looks at Justice, confused, as the Cruiser pulls away,
leaving Jay, Bob, Suzanne, and Banky. They start walking
down the lot.
BANKY
Well, boys--you're rich in love--
(indicating Jay)
Well, you're in love. And to top
that off, you've got your own monkey.
What more could two guys from Jersey
possibly want?
JAY
All those fucks to stop talking shit
about us on the Internet, for
starters.
BANKY
What do I keep telling you? There's
not much you can do to stop that.
Well, short of showing up at all
their houses and beating the shit
out of them, I guess.
Jay and Bob suddenly freeze. They look at each other and
smile.
JAY
(to Bob)
You know--with all that money we're
gonna make we can buy a lotta plane
tickets.
START THE JAY AND BOB KICKASS MONTAGE
EXT. SKY--DAY
A passenger JET flies through the sky.
EXT. SUBURBAN STREET--DAY
Jay and Bob stand across the street from a house. They check
the address on the big ream of paper they're carrying, nod
at each other, and cross the street.
INT. HOUSE--DAY
The doorbell rings. A MOTHER answers it to see Jay and Silent
Bob standing in the doorway.
MOTHER
Can I help you?
JAY
Yes. Ma'am, Does--
(reading of paper)
William Dusky live here?
MOTHER
Yes. He's my son.
JAY
May we talk to him, please.
MOTHER
One moment.
She walks away. After a beat, a fifteen-year-old KID comes
to the door.
KID
Yeah?
JAY
Yo--do you post as--
(reading off paper)
Magnolia-Fan on Movie Poop Shoot.com?
KID
Yeah.
JAY
And did you write "Fuck Jay and Silent
Bob. Fuck them up their stupid asses?
KID
Yeah, a while ago. So?
Jay and Bob nod at each other, then grab the KID, pull him
outside, and start beating the shit out of him on his front
lawn.
EXT. SKY--DAY
The passenger jet flies again, this time in the opposite
direction.
EXT. SUBURBAN HOUSE--DAY
Jay and Bob knocking at another door. Another MOTHER answers.
They speak, she heads inside, and another KID comes to the
door.
JAY
On Movie Poop Shoot.com. did you say
Jay and Silent Bob--
(reading off paper)
"--are fucking clown shoes. If they
were real, I'd beat the shit out of
them for being so stupid."
KID
(chuckling)
Yeah.
JAY
Really--
Again, Jay and Bob pull the Kid outside and beat the shit
out of him.
INT. CONVENIENCE STORE--DAY
Jay and Bob beat the shit out of a CLERK.
EXT. APARTMENT BUILDING HALLWAY--DAY
Jay and Bob beat the shit out of a WOMAN.
EXT. RECTORY--DAY
Jay and Bob beat the shit out of a PRIEST.
INT. OFFICE--DAY
Jay and Bob beat the shit out of a BUSINESSMAN.
EXT. MOVIE THEATRE--NIGHT
The marquee reads: JASON BIGGS AND JAMES VAN DER BEEK ARE
BLUNTMAN AND CHRONIC!
WORLD PREMIERE!
The front doors open and the CROWD lets out. First we see
DANTE and RANDAL.
RANDAL
Now that was worse then Clash of the
Titans.
DANTE
I still can't believe Judy Dench
played me.
RANDAL
Hey--remind me to renew that
restraining order.
DANTE
Why?
RANDAL
Because I'm gonna blast the flick on
the Internet tonight.
STEVE-DAVE and WALT exit.
STEVE-DAVE
Why can't Hollywood ever make a decent
comic book movie?
WALT
Tell'em Steve-Dave!
STEVE-DAVE
Would you stop saying that?
ALYSSA and TRISH come out.
TRISH
Well, that was just another paean to
male adolescence and its refusal to
grow up.
ALYSSA
Yeah, sis--but it was better than
Mallrats. At least Holden had the
good sense to keep his name off of
it.
TRISH
Why wouldn't Miramax option his other
comic instead? You know--the one he
drew about you and him and your
relationship?
ALYSSA
You mean Chasing Amy? That would
never work as a movie.
BANKY and HOOPER exit.
BANKY
I'm so fucking embarrassed--
HOOPER
Honey, you should be. They took your
characters and reduced them to one
ninety-minute-long-gay joke. It was
like watching Batman and Robin again.
BANKY
Thanks. That means a lot coming from
the guy who pretends to be Shaft as
opposed to the guy who takes shaft.
HOOPER
I don't hear you complaining nightly.
In fact, the only thing I do hear
you say is "Yes, Hooper! Cradle the
balls and work the shaft!"
BANKY
(looking around)
Hey! Hey! What'd we say? Not in
public!
A guy behind them calls out to Banks.
GUY
Nice movie, you fucking Tracer!
BANKY
(recognizing him)
You--!
GUY
That's right, you sonovabitch! I'm
back for round two!
Banky grabs the guy by the throat and starts choking him,
while Hooper tries to break them up.
WILLENHOLLY exits with Justice in hand-and leg cuffs and a
prison uniform.  They're flanked by two ARMED PRISON GUARDS.
WILLENHOLLY
You know, I don't get out to the
movies much. But I'd have to say
Bluntman and Chronic was Blunt-tastic!
JUSTICE
Are these leg cuffs really necessary?
WILLENHOLLY
Don't make me shoot you, Justice.
And finally, Jay and Silent Bob come out.
JAY
YO! THE PARTY'S ACROSS THE STREET,
FEATURING THE GREATEST BAND IN THE
WORLD: MORRIS DAY AND THE TIME!!!
WHIP PAN to Morris day and The Time on stage, performing
"The Bird." During the song, Morris points to--
Jay and Bob, who are dancing with Suzanne and Justice (who's
still in cuffs, flanked by the Guards). Jay looks to Bob,
they nod at each other and--
Jay and Silent Bob, join Morris Day and the TIME onstage,
and dance us out to the coda, which reads--
CODA
Bluntman and Chronic Strike Back went on to make a mere 2.3
million at the box office. It was the biggest commercial
failure in the history of Miramax films.  The film was roundly
drubbed as a bad idea by the denizens of the Internet chat
boards, and over the course of the next year, while they
waited for the Quick Stop restraining order to expire, Jay
and Silent Bob tracked them all down and beat the shit out
of them.
CREDITS. THEN--
INT. NOWHERE
A familiar WOMAN closes a book that's marked: THE VIEW
ASKEWNIVERSE. She puts the book down, smiles at us and skips
off.
THE END

lyrics.1144:
Fatalmente
Traté de elegir mis batallas hasta que las batallas me eligieron a mi
Miseria
Como la guerra de palabras que gritaba en mis sueños
Y tu pasaste justo por ahí
Estaba en el callejón, rodeada por todos lados
El cuchillo corta por ambos extremos
Si el zapato te queta, camina con él hasta que se rompan los tacones

Y me caí del pedestal
Directo a la madriguera del conejo
En pocas palabras, fue un mal momento
Empujada por el precipicio
Me aferré a los labios más cercanos
En pocas palabras, era el tipo equivocado

Ahora eres todo para mi
Eres todo para mi, ah
Sí, sí
Eres todo para mi, ah
Sí, sí

En realidad
Siempre sentí que me veía mejor por detrás
Extrañándome
En las puertas doradas de las que alguna vez ellos guardaban las llaves
Cuando solté mi espada
La tiré entre los arbustos y llamé a tu puerta
Y vivimos en paz
Pero si alguien viene por nosotros, esta vez, estoy lista

Y me caí del pedestal
Directo a la madriguera del conejo
En pocas palabras, fue un mal momento
Empujada por el precipicio
Me aferré a los labios más cercanos
En pocas palabras, era el tipo equivocado

Ahora eres todo para mi
Eres todo para mi, ah
Sí, sí
Eres todo para mi

No más llevar cuentas
Ahora solo te mantengo abrigado (Te mantengo abrigado)
No más tira y afloja
Ahora solo se que hay más (Se que hay más)
No más llevar cuentas
Ahora solo te mantengo abrigado (Te mantengo abrigado)
Y mis olas golpean tu costa
Siempre y para siempre

Yo del pasado
Quiero pedirte que no te pierdas en estas cosas insignificantes
Tus némesis
Se derrotarán a sí mismos antes de que tengas la oportunidad de golpear
Y él está pasando por aquí
Excepcional como el destello de un cometa en el cielo
Y él se siente como estar en casa
Si el zapato te queda, camina con él a donde sea que vayas

Y me caí del pedestal
Directo a la madriguera del conejo
En pocas palabras, fue un mal momento
Empujada por el precipicio
Escalé a la cima del acantilado
En pocas palabras, sobreviví

Ahora eres todo para mi
(Y ahora) Eres todo para mi, ah
(Y ahora) Eres todo para mi

Sí, sí
Eres todo para mi

Eres todo para mi

lyrics.1163:
Noviembre gris
He estado triste desde julio
La captura de movimiento
Me hizo ver mal
Repaso todos mis pasos en cada escalón
Intentando encontrar en cuál me equivoqué
Escribo cartas
Destinadas al fuego

Y recuperaba mi aliento
Mirando por una ventana abierta
Capturando mi muerte
Y no podía estar segura
Tuve un sentimiento tan particular
De que este dolor sería
Para siempre

Oye, diciembre
Creo que me siento sin ataduras
No puedo recordar
Por lo que solía pelear
Rebobino la cinta pero lo único que hace es pausarse
En el mismo momento, todo estaba perdido
Mandando señales
Para que me traicionaran

Y recuperaba mi aliento
Descalza en el invierno más frío
Capturando mi muerte
Y no podía estar segura
Tuve un sentimiento tan particular
De que este dolor sería
Para siempre
(para siempre)

No puedo pensar en todo el costo
Y las cosas que se perderán
Oh, ¿podemos tomarnos una pausa?
Para estar seguros, llegaremos a lo alto de nuevo
Ya sea el clima congelado
O la violencia de los días de perros
Estoy en las olas, siendo sacudido
¿Hay alguna línea que podría sólo cruzar?

Y cuando estaba en el naufragio (No puedo pensar en todo el costo)
Pensé en ti (Todas las cosas que se perderán ahora)
En las grietas de la luz (¿Podemos tomarnos una pausa?)
Soñé contigo (Para estar seguros, llegaremos a lo alto de nuevo, si piensas en todos los costos)
Fue lo suficientemente real (Ya sea el clima congelado)
Para ayudarme a salir adelante (O la violencia de los días de perros)
(Estoy en las olas, siendo sacudida)
(Estoy en las olas, siendo sacudida)
Juro que (¿Hay alguna línea que podría sólo cruzar?)
Estabas ahí

Y recuperaba mi aliento
El suelo de una cabaña crujiendo bajo mis pies
Y no podía estar segura
Tuve un sentimiento tan particular
Este dolor sería
Para siempre
Para siempre
Para siempre
Este dolor no sería
Para siempre

genius_description.97:
Ariana se une a Doja Cat y Megan Thee Stallion para un remix de “34 + 35”, el segundo sencillo de su sexto álbum de estudio"positions“.

El remix se anunció oficialmente el 13 de enero de 2021, después de que Ariana publicara un adelanto del remix e insinuara que habría dos artistas invitados en él.
Un día después, Ariana confirmo la presencia de las raperas Doja Cat y Megan Thee Stallion, publicando la portada oficial del remix en sus redes sociales.

On “F*CK YOU, GOODBYE,” The Kid LAROI and Machine Gun Kelly dive into their familiar relationship issues, as LAROI makes clear his discontent with his partner and his want to end their relationship. The two communicate their feelings over a guitar-based trap beat.

An early version of the song leaked in summer 2020 and was featured in episode 2 of the trailer for F*CK LOVE (SAVAGE), seemingly confirming its placement on the project.
genius_description.1247: “Last Christmas” is a song by Wham! It’s been widely covered by a mutlitude of artists, including Taylor Swift and Jimmy Eat World The song reached No. 1 in 2 countries and reached No. 2 in eight countries. Although often played during Christmas time, it is far from a Christmas themed song. It tells the story of a failed relationship and the sadness that the holiday triggers.

genius_description.1320:
“Chicken Noodle Soup” is a collaboration between Latin-American artist Becky G and j-hope, member of Korean boy group BTS, interpolating a mutual “favorite childhood song”. Naver reports it charted #1 in 69 countries on Apple Music upon release.

It interpolates the classic 2006 hit song “Chicken Noodle Soup” by Webstar and Young B (feat. AG aka The Voice of Harlem). j-hope says the song’s accompanying dance is one of the first songs that helped him realize his passion for it.

The song is a celebration of global diversity and culture, showing pride in where they came from. They rap and sing about their homes and how they got to be where they are now. In this track, they bring three languages together. They both connect on a classic African-American hip-hop song.

The music video seconds this: it features j-hope and Becky G alongside more than 50 culturally-diverse dancers to showcase an explosive, sharp-set choreography.
genius_description.49:
“Move Ya Hips” is a collaboration between A$AP Mob member A$AP Ferg, rap veteran Nicki Minaj and Atlanta rapper MadeinTYO.

Sonically, a light-sounding, sparkly trap beat sets the stage for MadeinTYO’s repetitive but catchy chorus. Heavier drums and bass are then brought into the two verses by New York natives Ferg and Nicki. The pair flow effortlessly, exchanging braggadocios bars packed full of wordplay. Minaj also adopts her quintessential formula of switching from a deep, low-octave voice to a much higher-pitched girly sounding vocal.

  


The song was first previewed by DJ Clue via Instagram Live on May 11, 2020. Nicki tweeted to fans, telling them to “light up Ferg’s comments everyday” if they wanted it to drop. Rapper and A$AP Mob member A$AP Rocky also co-signed the demand on July 26, which would precede Ferg’s official announcement about its imminent release less than 24 hours later.

This marks Ferg’s third collaboration with Nicki, with  the first two being 2017’s “Plain Jane REMIX” and the 2018’s “Runnin” for Creed II’s soundtrack. While also marking the fifth appearance with MadeinTYO—on “One Night Savage,” “Square Bitch,” “WAM” and their 2018 hit, “Ned Flanders.”
genius_description.50:
“Babushka” is Russian for “grandmother” or “elderly woman,” and it’s also a type of Russian headscarf tied under the chin, traditionally worn by women from Eastern Europe. In November 2018, A$AP Rocky appeared at the LACMA Art+Film Gala in Los Angeles, wearing a $495 Gucci babushka.

Rocky revealed more details about the fashion choice—and the inspiration for the song—in January 2019. Apparently, the decision stemmed from a desire to hide a cut on his face, which he touches on throughout the song’s lyrics, referencing the classic 1983 gangster film Scarface. In January 2019, he told GQ magazine:

[The song] was inspired by a situation I had where my face got cut, and I started walking around with a babushka to cover it. It was about last September. It started with a yellow one when I was on Trevor Noah’s show. I actually did a Vogue shoot the day after I got my face slashed.

Rocky first previewed “Babushka Boi” during his 2019 Injured Generation tour.
genius_description.66:
“Secreto” es una confesión de amor entre Karol G & Anuel AA donde admiten que han estado teniendo una relación secreta. Esta es su segunda canción juntos luego de “Culpables” hace unos meses.

Después de la primera colaboración, rumores empezaron a surgir de que si había una relación entre los artistas. Las sospechas fueron confirmadas cuando se dieron un beso en un concierto de Anuel en Nueva York.

Esta canción no fue anunciada de manera oficial, sin embargo, partes del tema empezaron a surgir en las redes. La canción fue filtrada por completo el 11 de diciembre del 2018, y lanzada oficialmente el 15 de enero del 2019.
genius_description.447:
Drake reunites with Atlanta trap artists Future and Young Thug for a tribute to the Atlanta rap collective D4L, which consisted of members Fabo, Mook-B, Stoney, and Shawty Lo.

The song is a remix of Dreezy’s and 2 Chainz‘ January 2018 track “2nd to None”–which was also produced by Southside.

Throughout the track, the trio represent their individual labels, Drake’s October’s Very Own (OVO), Future’s FreeBandz Gang (FBG), and Thugger’s Young Stoner Life Records (YSL), brag about their high-class lifestyles, and interpolate Drizzy’s iconic “what’s hannenin'?” from his June 2010 single with Lil Wayne, “Miss Me”—a line which was in turn borrowed from D4L’s November 2005 song, “I’m Da Man.”
genius_description.449:
Hate the way I miss you (short term Hate the way) is the first single off These Things Happen Too.

The song is about a relationship that didn’t went well but overall (said by G-Eazy in a interview) its about getting related to missing someone or something.
This features the long time collaborator blackbear who the two have worked together on songs such as Remember You.

This song was announced in early 2020 with a feature from late rapper Juice WRLD, however his feature was removed when the song released officially possibly due to his label wanting to use his verse for one of his many upcoming posthumous songs.

“These Things Happen Too” is the sequel of his 2014 success album “These Things Happen”. We will probably get back an old G-Eazy, with nostalgic songs like this single.
We already teased the album by doing as blackbear feature like he did on the presequel.
genius_description.476: H.E.R takes it back and samples Herb Alpert’s 1987 hit “Making Love in the Rain” on her rnb jam “Damage”. On the track she expresses how she doesn’t want to be taken for granted by her lover and how they need to be careful with her because they could hurt her .
genius_description.477:
The Compton rapper, YG assists H.E.R on this song in the attempts of showcasing two sides to her supposed new perspectives on love and relationships.
The first being that she is slowly coming out of the shadows following her often anonymity in which she clearly portrays this by her frequent use of sun glasses so as to hide her eyes from the general public and love in general but this time even from the music video, her contact with the camera which is portrayed as the lover shows her steady movement to being less anonymous and more willing to show love.
The second is how she tries to show her loving and presumably sexual side and this is due to the 97 bpm that the song is done in in the B major key.
genius_description.503:
On “Lion King on Ice,” J. Cole reverts to his alter ego, Young Simba, but now in a much colder and darker tone. He raps about his come-up and his experience growing up in Fayetteville, where he wasn’t always certain that he would see the next day. He furthers this by reflecting on the challenges he has endured in his career and realizing that his fame and wealth haven’t erased the trauma of his past.

Parts of the song are rapped from the perspective of a young Cole, as he raps about needing to prove himself and rise to the top of the rap game, both of which the current Cole has already accomplished.

Two days before releasing this song, Cole published an essay titled “The Audacity” in which he discussed how the feeling of needing to prove himself is what drove him when he first began rapping:

When I started rapping, it was the competition that drove me. I had a burning desire to be the best in the world and to prove it with every verse.

This and “The Climb Back” were initially the first two singles from Cole’s album, The Fall Off, and were released together as Lewis Street. However, the latter was relocated to The Off-Season in May 2021.
genius_description.504:
J. Cole’s first offering of 2019 serves as a warning in advance of an extensive rollout of Dreamville material. On the track, Cole envisions himself in the center of the old and new generations of hip-hop, therefore making him the “middle child” of rap.

“Middle Child Syndrome” is a psychological condition in which middle children sometimes feel neglected by their families due to the attention that their younger and older siblings receive.
genius_description.505:
“Snow on tha Bluff” is J. Cole’s first release of 2020. On the song, which is titled after a January 2011 film about a robbery in Atlanta, Cole delivers a single continuous verse that speaks on various issues facing the United States, including police brutality, wealth inequality, and racism. He also asks for his fans not to idolize him, wanting to instead be perceived as a regular person.

Although not explicitly stated, the first part of the track is likely a response to Noname’s perceived criticisms of Cole on Twitter. She has frequently stated that she is against capitalism and celebrity culture, two things that Cole raps about in his verse.

The artwork displays the beginning of the verse. The date at the top, June 4, 2020, likely indicates the day the song was written. This date is several days after Cole was seen protesting racial injustice in his hometown, Fayetteville, NC.
genius_description.507: “Need Me” is New York rapper, J.I’s breakthrough single. Backed by a bouncy upbeat instrumental, J.I. has his eyes set on a girl–who hasn’t been dating for a while because her exes “did [her] wrong”. Knowing he’s “too official” to “stress a bitch”, he tells her that she can call his phone when she needs him.
genius_description.668:
On “GO,“ The Kid LAROI teams up with his late mentor and labelmate Juice WRLD. On the track, both artists talk about their personal struggles with girls and drugs, whilst also touching on their fast paced lives.

The track leaked on YouTube on April 18, 2020, and was later confirmed in the comment section of LAROI’s Instagram post to be  released alongside a music video. However, the leaked version featured a different first verse from LAROI, and he explained the reason for the change in a livestream on Caffeine, on June 12th, 2020, saying:

I wanted to keep it the way that we made it, ‘cause […] I put the [leaked] verse on after Juice had passed. And it just felt bad to not do it like the original was and put it out like that. So, that’s why you guys didn’t get the “leaked version.“ I know that maybe you guys think the leaked one was better. But this is the original one.
genius_description.693:
In “Leave Em Alone”, Layton Greene enlists Lil Baby, PnB Rock and female duo City Girls to drop an exclusive romantic banger.

She talks about how she can’t leave this one dude alone and that she caught feelings for him.

This is the first Layton Greene and Lil Baby collaboration and it was also featured on QC’s compilation album “Quality Control: Control the Streets Vol. 2”

As of July 2020, they’ve seen a recent resurgence in popularity thanks to video sharing app  TikTok
genius_description.793: Smile is just a feel good song about living your best life and not giving a fuck about the haters.
genius_description.958: “Walk Me Home” is a song by American singer-songwriter P!nk, released as the lead single from her 2019 album Hurts 2B Human. The lead single and album was first revealed in an appearance on The Ellen DeGeneres Show on February 6, 2019.
genius_description.1082:
“Relación” es un tema que originalmente habla de una relación fallida entre un hombre y una mujer. Le despreocupación del hombre por la relación hizo que la mujer se cansara de él y a raíz de esto ella se aventura a vivir su vida y los roles cambian. Ahora es el hombre quien quiere volver, pero ya es muy tarde y la mujer no tiene interés ninguno en recuperar la relación.

La intención de hacerle un remix fue dada a conocer por Sech, quien el 22 de junio de 2020 publicó un video en Instagram cantando “Relación” y preguntando lo siguiente:

Si algún día hiciera este REMIX Y TU FUERAS EL PRODUCTOR CON QUIEN SERÍA ? 👇👇

El colombiano Keityn comentó esta publicación, sugiriendo que uno de los artistas con los que usualmente trabaja hace parte de la remezcla. El 28 de junio el panameño volvió a pedirle a sus fanáticos que le recomienden un artista para el remix, pero esta vez confirmándolo.

El primer confirmado fue J Balvin, siendo el mismo Sech el que compartió un adelanto de su participación en el remix
genius_description.1116:
“Adicto”, que fue rumoreada como un sencillo del álbum Los Dioses, marca otra de las tantas colaboraciones entre los reggaetoneros puertorriqueños.

Anuel AA y Ozuna se juntan una vez más para cantarle al amor de dos personas que quieren estar juntos, pero no saben cómo amarse. Haciendo referencia en el coro de esta de que por más que se quiera aceptar que es imposible, siguen buscándose el uno al otro.
genius_description.1194:
The Weeknd links up with pop singer and past collaborator Ariana Grande for the remix of his hit track “Save Your Tears” from his 2020 record-breaking album After Hours.

On April 19, 2021, a snippet of the remix was shared by both Ariana Grande and The Weeknd via their social media accounts, with audio showing both of them harmonizing. Ariana later announced via Instagram that the song would officially be dropping on the same week. Both artists confirmed that the song would be released on April 23, 2021.
genius_description.1237:
“A BOY IS A GUN*” is one of the more Kanye-esque tracks out of IGOR, as seen by Tyler’s delivery of the chorus and the clear use of “Bound” by the Ponderosa Twins, which was also sampled by West in his 2013 album, Yeezus. The song was first teased in a 28-second snippet posted by Tyler on May 13, 2019. It is one of the softer cuts on the album with the chorus featuring prominent use of a soul sample, with glittery synths and keys littered throughout the background.

Tyler seems to be alluding to his possible bisexuality, with the lyrical similes of his lover being like a gun and the title of the track being “A BOY IS A GUN*.” Throughout the song, Tyler compares being with his love interest with gun ownership in several ways.

The title “A BOY IS A GUN*” was inspired by the 1971 French western movie A Girl Is a Gun which Tyler confirmed at the IGOR Apple Music concert.

The song’s music video was released on September 16th, 2019.
genius_description.1238:
“EARFQUAKE” is a collaboration between Tyler, The Creator and Playboi Carti. In the song, Tyler sings about a lover he depends on, who he knows he hasn’t treated the best, but needs. This is done over beautiful, cheery piano chords and heavy, distorted drums, mixing styles from his last two albums, Cherry Bomb and Flower Boy.

In an interview with Rick Rubin on his podcast Broken Record, Tyler explains that his inspiration for the title came from there being an actual earthquake when he was writing the song. Then he decided to change the “th” to an “f.”

During Tyler’s concert hosted by Apple Music with IGOR presentation, Tyler said the song is from 2017, and he wrote it for Justin Bieber, but “he didn’t take it.” It was also offered to Rihanna who also declined.
genius_description.1239:
“I THINK” questions both Tyler’s mental state and his feelings in a romantic relationship. Tyler doesn’t know whether to continue to be vulnerable, because of his partner’s actions and their effect on Tyler, but his curiosity grows and latches on to the bond he has created with this person. This pushes him to believe in love. This develops the theme of love throughout the album, as introduced in the previous track.

Tyler released “a fraction of” the music video for the track on October 24th, 2019.
genius_description.1240:
“IGOR’S THEME,” the introductory track to the project, was first teased in a 50-second snippet posted on Tyler’s social media platforms on May 1, 2019, shortly after  speculation arose surrounding the album after the release of a Sony Financial Report. The track also features additional guest vocals from Lil Uzi Vert and Solange.

Tyler uses this track primarily to let the listener know what they are getting into by indulging in this album, and that they will indeed, “feel this one,” if they weren’t expecting to do so already. The track opens with a distorted bass playing one note for 24 seconds. This same bass sound reappears in some shape or form on every song on the album.
genius_description.1241:
On “NEW MAGIC WAND,” Tyler desperately attempts to convince someone he has feelings for to not leave him. However, the person Tyler is in love with is still thinking about their previous relationship with a woman. In the song, Tyler goes to extreme length such as threatening to kill both his love interest and his love interest’s ex-girlfriend in order to get what he wants.

On September 12, 2020, Tyler determined that “NEW MAGIC WAND” is his best song ever in a tweeted bracket ranking of all his own favorite songs.  The song beat out OKAGA, CA for the number one spot.  Tyler had previously declared it his favorite song on IGOR through Instagram on May 30, 2019.

The song was first teased in a 47-second snippet posted on Tyler’s social media platforms on May 14, 2019. The song opens with grimy beat, and features a soft synth change during the bridge.

Tyler also referenced this track in a numerous tweets[1][2] before the album released.

https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/1128345413822500864

The song features Jessy Wilson and Santigold.

https://twitter.com/tylerthecreator/status/1130136278115201026
genius_description.1242: “PUPPET” is the second collaboration between Tyler, the Creator and Kanye West, the first being on “SMUCKERS” from Cherry Bomb. The track discusses the obsessive and protective nature of being in love, and how controlling it can be. Here Tyler/IGOR acknowledges both the positive and negative sides of being under your lover’s thumb. This is thematically represented in the disjointed second half of the song, where music from the start of the song abruptly cuts in.
genius_description.1243:
“RUNNING OUT OF TIME” describes Tyler’s fleeting relationship with a significant other and warn them that a split is imminent.

Thematically, it introduces tension to the love dynamic previously constructed throughout the album.

During Tyler’s Apple Music Concert in L.A, he explained that he showed the album to Kendrick Lamar, where Kendrick praised him about the raw feeling of the album and his overall willingness to ‘sing his truth’. This conversation led him to write this song.
genius_description.1244:
“WHAT’S GOOD” is the ninth track from Tyler’s fifth studio album IGOR. It was first teased in a 48-second snippet posted on Tyler’s social media platforms on May 3, 2019, showing him dancing frantically to the song.

The track makes heavy use of drums and distorted synths, one of the more aggressive cuts from the album. It is also one of the only tracks that Tyler raps throughout.

Up-and-coming UK rapper slowthai, who also released an album on May 17, provides additional vocals for the track.
genius_description.1258:
“Go Loko” serves as the second single of YG’s fourth studio album 4REAL 4REAL. On the Jon Z and Tyga assisted track, the rappers describe their wild lifestyles and discuss various topics including their relationships, alcohol, and weapons.

“Loco” is a Spanish term that translates to crazy, which fits the song’s overall theme of going out of control. YG chooses not to spell “loco” correctly, by replacing the ‘c’ with a ‘k’, because of his affiliation with the Blood gang and their rivalry with the Crip gang. YG has done this before on his album My Krazy Life.
genius_description.1261:
“223’s” is a bouncy, joyful collaboration between young rappers YNW Melly and 9LOKKNINE. The song features production from New Jersey producer Rocco Did It Again.

The song was originally released as a song on 9LOKK’s 2018 mixtape Lil Glokk That Stole Christmas, with 9LOKK being credited as the lead artist and Melly being listed as a feature. Later, on August 9, 2019, the song was re-released as a single, with Melly now being the lead artist and 9LOKK listed as the featured artist.

The song has since peaked at number 34 on the Billboard Hot 100, particularly due to a dance challenge that has gone viral on social media app TikTok.

The music video for the track, directed by DrewFilmedIt, was released on November 2, 2019. Melly reacted to the video from his jail cell over a FaceTime call with DJ Akademiks.

The track appeared on Melly’s debut studio album Melly Vs. Melvin, which released on November 22, 2019.
genius_description.27: a parody of the song mood but made in roblox
genius_description.68:
“China” is a super union between cultures and genres of Puerto Rico and Colombia. The song is about a person who let himself cope with the atmosphere of having a good time living on the album and took time with his partner to celebrate.

This song is a clear tribute to Shaggy’s song “It Wasn’t Me” which is a classic that has been used as a reference in many themes, such as “Va Segui” by Mark B, a song with which “China” It was strongly compared a month before its release because they both had similar rhythms.

The owner of the song is Anuel, he named the song himself, but it means nothing. There were many rumors that the name was given because in Puerto Rico, green is known as Chinese color. On the other hand, the song is called China since the original track (Produced by DJ Snake) had Asian features according to Anuel and that’s why he put it that way.

If we talk about the production, in the first instance, the producer of this song was going to be DJ Snake, who for several paperwork problems with Anuel could not be included, then, he had to change to the producer that today is Tainy, so same as the instruments of this one had to be changed. All this based on what Anuel said in an interview for MTV.

It should be noted that in most of the issues that Anuel has launched this 2019 he has been involved with his girlfriend and future wife Karol G. According to rumors, Anuel had said at the beginning of the year that Karol G was going to be the only female that he was going to collaborate with, despite seeing him with Becky G in Bubalu.

Originally, in the song they were going to be all these artists except J Balvin, this one was added at the last minute. From what you can see in the video, the shots where Balvin appears were recorded in Cartagena, where he was alone.

So much so that there are several scenes where a green screen was used to pretend that Balvin was on set with the others:
genius_description.69:
BIENVENIDO AL CALENDARIO DE SENCILLOS DE GENIUS EN ESPAÑOL

Esta página agrupa los sencillos musicales en español de artistas reconocidos que se han lanzado oficialmente o filtrado a lo largo de la semana.

No se permite la auto-promoción, publicación de temas falsos o no relevantes.

genius_description.100:
Para la séptima pista de su sexto álbum de estudio, positions, Ariana recluta al rapero Ty Dolla $ign. “safety net” marca la primera colaboración entre los dos artistas. En una entrevista, $ign habla de la pista llamándola “una melodía melódica y sorprendente”.

A principios de octubre, los rumores de la colaboración circularon en las redes luego de que se filtrara el supuesto tracklist del álbum con un nombre diferente como “sin remedio”. Y el 24 de octubre de 2020, Ariana subió a su Twitter una foto del tracklist del álbum, confirmando así la colaboración y el título del tema.
genius_description.109:
Benvenuti/e!

Lungo tutto l'anno, grazie ad alcune stazioni radio, a YouTube, alle ore di ricerca su questo sito e ad alcuni dei suoi utenti, ho avuto accesso ad una quantità enorme sia di musica nuova, sia di musica… non così nuova: considerando che la maggior parte dei brani ascoltati mi sono piaciuti e che quello appena trascorso è un anno speciale, visto che stiamo entrando in una nuova decade, ho deciso di provare a fare qualcosa di diverso dal mio solito.

Vediamo se, tentando di classificare i migliori pezzi “internazionali” (che commenterò in inglese) e quelli nazionali (che commenterò in italiano), oltre ad aggiungere alcune sorprese, ho fatto un buon lavoro…

Buona lettura! : )



Welcome!

Throughout the whole year, thanks to some radio stations, to YouTube, to the hours of research on this site and to some of its users, I’ve been able to listen to a huge amount of either new and… “not so new” music: considering that I liked the most part of the songs I’ve listened to and that 2019 is a special year, as we’re entering in a new decade, I’ve decided to try something different from my standards.

Let’s see if, by trying to rank the best “international” songs (which I’ll comment in English) and the best national ones (which I’ll comment in Italian), besides of adding some surprises, I’ve done a good job…

Enjoy! : )
genius_description.110:
“Supalonely”, albümün üçüncü şarkısıdır. Şarkı, TikTok‘ta viral olduktan sonra Mart 2020'de popülerlik kazandı.

Şarkı, BENEE'nin bir ayrılık sonrasında Los Angeles'a yaptığı bir gezi sırasında yazıldı. Verdiği bir röportajda şarkısı hakkında açıklamada bulunmuştur:

Bazen üzgün olduğunda, üstesinden gelmeye bakmalısın. “Supalonely” dinlediğimde üzgünlüğüm gidiyor, garip bir şekilde iyi hissetmeye başlıyorum."
genius_description.114: Billie Eilish is on top of the Hottest 50!
genius_description.127:
A compilation of my favorite songs, albums, verses and moments in the music world, 2019

Soon
genius_description.152:
favoritos 2020




  


En “favoritos 2020” escribiré mi carta de despedida hacia este horrible –pero retrospectivo– año enfocándome en el apartado musical.

En esta página se encuentra:


Una lista de las canciones lanzadas este año que más me gustaron
Dos top 10: uno para los álbumes que más me gustaron y otro para los EP
Mi año musical en Spotify (o mi Spotify Wrapped, llámalo como quieras)
Una lista totalmente desordenada con álbumes, mixtapes o EP lanzados antes de este año y que les di una oportunidad justo en 2020.



Todo el contenido en esta página se basa meramente en mis gustos; si tú tienes otros gustos musicales y te apetece compartirlos con el resto de nuestra comunidad puedes crear tu propia página de fin de año. 🤠

  


Puedes visitar la edición anterior a esta página, “favoritos 2019”, cliqueando aquí.
genius_description.162:
“MOOD 4 EVA” is the twelfth track on Beyoncé’s specially-curated The Lion King accompaniment  project, The Gift, and functions as a celebratory anthem. It features JAY-Z and her Lion King co-star, Childish Gambino, as well as a tropical afrobeat instrumental produced by Just Blaze and DJ Khaled.

The song samples Grammy Award-winning Malian songstress Oumou Sangaré’s classic 1989 love song, titled “Diaraby Nene”:

https://youtu.be/i_Sid8WDOno
genius_description.163: Le 19 Juillet 2019, Beyoncé sort un nouvel album nommé “The Lion King: The Gift” à l'occasion de la sortie du chef-d'œuvre de Disney en film.
genius_description.193:
WELCOME TO GENIUS' OCTOBER 2019 SINGLES RELEASE CALENDAR!!!



For October 2019 album releases, visit this page



This page highlights the notable singles released in all genres throughout October 2019. Each song title includes a hyperlink to the corresponding lyric page.

HOW CAN YOU HELP?


Adding songs



If there’s a notable song you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you notice that any of the songs on this list haven’t been transcribed, go to the corresponding page and add in lyrics!


Updating dates



If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.
genius_description.218:
Through the Genius x Spotify integration, Genius is at your fingertips when and where you experience music. In the Spotify iPhone app, Genius knowledge is stripped down to its essence with a new product called the Fact Track – a Genius-powered experience that plays along with the music, revealing lyrics, fun facts, and artist stories.

Behind The Lyrics: The Complete Experience is a Spotify playlist and one-stop-shop to all existing Fact Tracks with new songs being added each week!

Click on the playlist on your iPhone and watch your screen as you listen to see lyrics, fun facts, and artist stories!

https://open.spotify.com/user/genius_official/playlist/40kuKKPyHuKDnqpIa8Cgb6

What if I have an Android or something?

You’re in luck: you can also watch Fact Tracks on Genius.com on your laptop! Just:


Choose a song from this list.
Make sure Spotify is open (download it here).
Click on the media dropdown menu below the song artwork in the right column and click on Fact Track (on mobile, it’s located at the bottom of the page). It looks like this: 

Enjoy! If you’re on mobile, the button will take you to the Spotify playlist and you’ll have to play a song manually.



To Learn more about the Genius x Spotify integration, check out the announcement post here.
genius_description.303: This is DaBaby. The essential tracks, all in one playlist.
genius_description.372: آهنگ “آدمای خوشگل” سومین ترک از آلبوم “پروژه ی همکاری شماره 6” ادشیرن هستش که در سال 2019 منتشر شد، مضمون و موضوع کلی آهنگ راجب این هستش که خودمون باشیم و سعی نکنیم مثل آدمای به اصطلاح خوشگل و پولدار رفتار کنیم و ادای اونارو در بیاریم، مفهومی که با دیدن موزیک ویدیو هم میتونین اونو درک کنین
genius_description.388:
Eminem bu parçada, geçmişteki zorluklardan bahsediyor ve “geriye dönme şansı olsaydı bugüne kadar yaptığı her şeyi tekrar yapacağının” farkında oluşunu anlatıyor. Yükselen yıldız Don Toliver, şarkıyı iç gözlemsel bir bakış açısıyla yaklaşan bir nakarat ile süslüyor.

Eminem ayrıca yakın zamanda gerçekleşen ve halen daha tam olarak sonlanmayan atışmalarından da konu açıyor ve Nick Cannon, Machine Gun Kelly ve Tyler, The Creator gibi rapçilere sesleniyor.

Şarkının prodüksiyonu D.A. Doman'a ait. Sert vuruşlu enstrümanlar kullanmasıyla bilinen Doman, Eminem'i modern trap stiline uygun bir ortama sokuyor. Bu şarkı aynı zamanda Doman'ın Those Kinda Nights ve Godzilla parçalarıyla birlikte albümdeki üçüncü iş birliği.
genius_description.392: Eminem, “You Gon' Learn” parçasında Royce da 5'9" ve White Gold ile takım oluyor ve esneklik ile kararlılığın önemini vurgulamak istiyor. Royce ve Em, karşı karşıya kaldıkları çirkin olaylara ve sıkıntılara, yıldızlığa doğru çıktıkları bu yolculukta savaştıkları şeytanların farkındalar ve kendilerini bu savaşta hayatta kalanlar olarak tanımlıyorlar.

Eminem'in Leaving Heaven şarkısı albümdeki
kişisel olarak en duygusal şarkısıdır. Eminem geçmişindeki
yaşadıklarının bugün onu nasıl şekillendirdiğini anlatırken,
onu 1 yaşana girerken terk eden ve geçen sene vefat eden

kendisi harika bir yazar, harika bir ses. Love the way you lie

genius_description.394:
В своём интервью для KXNG Crooked Эминем рассказал о том, что заметил Young M.A, когда сёрфил в интернете. Она сразу приглянулась ему своим стилем, и Эм пригласил её на свой альбом.

Их коллаб на MTBMB идёт вторым треком, Маршалл специально хотел поставить трек с ней сразу после интро, что бы “устроить разнос”.

В этом треке Эминем обрушивается на игру, словно Танос. Вооружённый своей спорной лирикой, в этом треке он упоминает самых известных террористов, сравнивая себя с ними,  а так же возвращается к бифу с MGK.
genius_description.455:
“Lost in the Fire” is a collaboration between French DJ Gesaffelstein and Canadian singer The Weeknd.

On the song, Abel sings about his tumultuous relationship with girlfriend Bella Hadid, assuring her that he “can’t lose” her again. He also sings, in explicit detail, about his illustrious sex life with Bella and other lovers. The “fire” is the time period between their initial breakup and reconnection.

“Lost in the Fire” found additional interest when lyrics in Abel’s first verse were interpreted as shots at Drake.

The track was first teased by Gesaffelstein on January 7, 2019. Abel continued to tease the song on his social media over the next three days. The song ultimately debuted on the third episode of The Weeknd’s Beats 1 Radio show Memento Mori, which aired at midnight on January 11, 2019.
genius_description.511:
On “GATTI,” Travis Scott and rising Brooklyn rapper Pop Smoke team up for the first time on the JACKBOYS record.

On December 23, 2019, a video of Pop Smoke and Travis Scott hanging out in the streets circulated online, featuring a snippet of an unreleased track between the two artists. A day later, UK drill producer 808Melo confirmed a collaboration between the two, revealing that Mike Dean was mastering the track.

An early demo of the track featuring French Montana leaked on October 28, 2019.

On December 30, 2019, Travis Scott released accompanying visuals for the track, which featured Travis and Pop Smoke driving around Houston in a Bugatti Veyron.

genius_description.594:
“Get Me” es el segundo sencillo del quinto álbum de estudio de Justin Bieber, Changes. Fue lanzado en streaming al mismo tiempo que el título oficial del álbum y la portada. En la pista, Bieber y la intérprete de R&B Kehlani cantan en un formato de llamada y respuesta sobre su relación figurativa y la compatibilidad de los dos.

La canción continúa la sensación de R&B que Bieber ha prometido para su quinto álbum de estudio, con el dúo cantando muy sexualmente con un ritmo sombrío que presenta muchas percusiones artificiales y bajos, las principales características del genero.

La existencia de “Get Me” se dio a conocer el día anterior a su lanzamiento oficial, ya que se mostró en una lista tentativa junto con varias otras canciones en la serie documental del cantante, Justin Bieber: Seasons.
genius_description.595: “Forever” es una canción del quinto álbum de estudio de Justin Bieber, Changes. La canción se lanzó por primera vez el 24 de diciembre de 2019, a través de un avance de su álbum en YouTube que reproducía un fragmento de la canción. El 4 de enero de 2020, más de dos minutos de la pista se filtró en sitios web.

genius_description.716:
Lil Baby and DaBaby team up on “Baby,” a song which marks their third official collaboration following “Baby Shower” and “Today (Remix).” Released as a single for Quality Control’s compilation album Control the Streets, Vol. 2, “Baby” turned out to be the most popular track on the project—it performed high on the charts and was supported by the release of a music video that has quickly garnered tens of millions of views.

On the Wheezy-produced track, the two “Baby” artists trade bars about their upbringing, accomplishments, and relationships with women. The two artists rap about representing their respective cities and address their lifestyle: their tough come-up in a difficult environment has left its marks on their daily lives, which are marked by dangerousness and opulence.
genius_description.855: “Light It Up” is a party track that brings together Marshmello with Tyga and Chris Brown. This marks the first collaboration between the three and reunites Tyga and Brown for the first time since their 2015 project Fan of a Fan: The Album.

genius_description.918:
NAV and Gunna reunite with Travis Scott on “Turks,” the second collaboration between the three artists all on the song, following the featured artist’s August 2018 song, “YOSEMITE.” The three artists have also each collaborated individually with one another, as detailed below in the Q&A. This song also serves as the lead single to NAV’s third studio album, Good Intentions.

The title of this song refers to Turks & Caicos, which are a group of islands that are located southeast of the British Overseas Territory. The three artists tell a rags-to-riches story over the Wheezy-produced upbeat tune, discussing the transition from them being poor to eventually living a lavish lifestyle. They drop references to many expensive items that they possess, including cars, drugs, jewelry, weaponry, and women.

This song’s official music video premiered on NAV’s YouTube channel three days after its release, on March 30, 2020. Young Thug, a close friend and frequent collaborator of the three artists, makes a cameo appearance. The video was directed by NAV’s XO Records founder and manager, Amir “Cash” Esmailian.

genius_description.962:
“Hey Look Ma, I Made It” is a tongue-in-cheek celebration of Brendon Urie’s success in the music industry.

As a teenager, Urie’s parents were afraid for his future as a starving artist. Having reached financial stability as a musician, Urie tips his hat to his mother, and reflects on his journey to success, examining the thirst of record labels for new material and the quest to avoid people, who only want to be associated with him due to his fame.
genius_description.963:
“High Hopes” is about seeking your dreams without hesitancy and seeing those dreams come to fruition beyond your wildest imagination. Having high hopes is a phrase that means to have:

a strong feeling that something good will happen or be true

Throughout Panic! At The Disco’s and Brendon Urie’s career, the band has faced challenges and changes. The beginning of Panic!’s journey was fraught with financial challenges. Brendon Urie, trying to make ends meet, worked in a Smoothie King to support his music career. While creating their iconic “I Write Sins Not Tragedies”, the band could not afford to pay professional string musicians, leaving them to record a middle school band member playing the part one note at a time.

Even with commercial success, the trials of the music industry still plagued the band. From band members leaving and attempting to adapt to a turbulent music scene, Brendon Urie has seen his dream of maintaining success in the music industry fade in and out of view. Despite these difficulties, Urie, now the last remaining member of the band, has continued to strive for his goals and has earned a Grammy nomination, a stint on the Broadway show Kinky Boots, and numerous other accolades.

Upon the song’s release, Brendon revealed his inspiration behind “High Hopes” on Twitter and Instagram, and in the video description on YouTube

I spent too long not setting my expectations high enough, worried about how it felt to fail. I hit a point when I realized I had to aim high and fail, fail, fail in order to keep growing. This one is for all of you who helped me go for it all. I thank you.
- B

The song was released half an hour prior to the due time – 2pm EST – on the official Panic! At The Disco YouTube Channel, racking up just over 1k views, before being officially released via a separate video, and on Spotify.

“High Hopes” is the third single released from Pray For The Wicked. It was preceded by “Say Amen (Saturday Night)” and “(Fuck a) Silver Lining” which were released two months earlier.

“High Hopes” is the highest charting song in Panic! At the Disco history, peaking at number 4 on the Billboard Hot 100, surpassing “I Write Sins Not Tragedies” at number 7 in 2006.
genius_description.964:
“Into the Unknown” is a cover of the soundtrack’s lead song from the animated Disney musical Frozen II (2019). The song was released by American band Panic! at the Disco as the album’s first single roughly two weeks before the film’s November 22, 2019, release date.

In the movie, the song is originally sung by Idina Menzel, the actress who voices the main character, Elsa, and features Norwegian singer-songwriter AURORA.

According to Billboard, the original song “[gives] voice to a conflicted Elsa as she debates whether to take off on yet another adventure to save the kingdom of Arendelle.”
genius_description.1020:
El artista estadounidense Post Malone se une a la estrella en ascenso DaBaby en “Enemies”, la pista número 3 de Hollywood’s Bleeding. En el transcurso de la canción, analiza la forma en que la fama de artista comercial ha afectado sus relaciones y cómo responde a la deslealtad, mientras que DaBaby rapea sobre su nuevo éxito y envía algunas líneas de advertencia dirigidas a sus enemigos.

DaBaby mostró una parte de su verso y un fragmento del estribillo en su cuenta de Instagram, una hora antes del lanzamiento de la canción.

Esta pista marca la primera vez que Post Malone y DaBaby han trabajado juntos.
genius_description.1021:
“Die For Me” es la pista número 7 en el tercer álbum del artista estadounidense Post Malone, Hollywood’s Bleeding.

La pista es una mezcla entre pop y trap que nos muestra a Post y a Future lamentando sus relaciones con mujeres en las que no confían, mientras que Halsey muestra el punto de vista de una mujer sobre el tema.

Esta canción marca la primera colaboración de Post Malone con Halsey y su segunda con Future, quien ya había aparecido en el remix de “Congratulations”.
genius_description.1023:
“Take What You Want” jest pierwszą współpracą amerykańskiego rapera-piosenkarza Posta Malone'a pomiędzy liderem legendarnego, brytyjskiego zespołu rockowego Black Sabbath, Ozzym Osbournem oraz druga z Travisem Scottem, poprzedzająca ich siły połączone wraz z DJ Khaledem w nagraniu “Celebrate” pochodzącym z jego jedenastego albumu studyjnego, Father of Asahd (2019).

W utworze trzej narratorzy opowiadają o źle zakończonym związku miłosnym, w którym Malone i Osbourne skupiają się na bagażach emocjonalnych ich znaczących, drugich połówek, za to Scott zagłębia się w specyfikach ów więzi, w tym używkach, tj. alkohol czy narkotyki i stosunkach seksualnych.

“Power Is Power” is the third single for the Game of Thrones album For the Throne.

The title is a reference to a scene that took place in the first episode of the show’s second season. The scene consists of Littlefinger telling Cersei Lannister “Knowledge is power,” which she responds to by telling him that “Power is power.”

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zdRJybJ047I&feature=youtu.be&t=107

The theme of the song explains that those who possess the power to survive and rule over others will only continue to grow stronger through their trials. This is a theme commonly seen throughout the story line of Game of Thrones

SZA had teased the song two days before the release, by posting the official cover art on Instagram.

genius_description.1110: Liam released this playlist on Spotify and updates it every now and again with his favorites songs at the moment. his last update was on May 29, 2019.
genius_description.1144:
“long story short” es una descripción rápida de las demonizaciones públicas que Taylor ha experimentado desde su enemistad con Kanye West en 2016. El drama ha sido objeto de numerosas canciones de Taylor, apareciendo desde su sexto álbum de estudio, reputation. Sin embargo, “long story short” ofrece una confirmación de resolución y paz, y Taylor finalmente se siente segura de que esa etapa de su vida ha disminuido.

“long story short” es una oda particular al novio actual de Taylor, Joe Alwyn, con quien comenzó a salir en la época del drama. Con la crónica de un puñado de canciones de Taylor, “long story short” enfatiza aún más que Alwyn siempre ha sido su “lugar seguro” durante la confusión.
genius_description.1163:
El último track de la edición estándar de Evermore es una balada de piano meditativa que rastrea el viaje del narrador desde un período aparentemente interminable de profunda depresión y dolor hasta un lugar de esperanza.

Evermore marca la segunda colaboración de Justin Vernon con Taylor Swift. Taylor y Justin trabajaron juntos en su álbum anterior, folklore para la cuarta canción del álbum, “exile”.

“evermore” trata con temas de salud mental, aunque esta pista presenta un camino más lineal hacia la curación.
genius_description.1165:
Hey, All!

In my 2019 Listening Log, I will really only put songs I’ve streamed over 30 Times in 2019. Also, since 2019 is the final year of the 2010s decade, I’m streaming every single song of this decade that I had in my Spotify library like they just recently came out to bring in the 2020s! Those songs will get honorable mentions as I only tend to stream the most relevant songs that came out within a 6 month period. After they’re 6 months old or I just can’t vibe to them anymore, I recycle them to this playlist and they are removed from my Main Library.

Thanks for checking it out!

genius_description.1314:
“365” is a collaboration between Zedd and Katy Perry. The track was originally confirmed by Zedd  in August 2018 and later registered online in January 2019.

It was rumored that the release date for “365” would be February 7th, 2019, but the song was actually released on February 14th after Katy teased the music video on Instagram with the caption “Valentine’s Day is going to be extra obsessive this year”.
genius_description.1315:
Producer ​benny blanco teams with Juice WRLD as well as Panic! at the Disco singer Brendon Urie on “Roses,” a highly-emotional ballad of love and loss.

Released on December 5, 2018, “Roses” represents a unique trend of rappers teaming up with alternate rock artists and blurring the boundaries between their genres. Juice WRLD puts his flexibility on full display, able to blend his music perfectly with Urie’s outstanding vocals.
genius_description.1316:
“Eastside” focuses on the relationship of two people who fall in love. It follows them as they go through their relationship and as they reminisce about their memories together.

The song marks the debut of the multi-award winning songwriter, producer and musician Benny Blanco, featuring Khalid and Halsey. Its release was first hinted at by some of his fans on Twitter, just days before its release. Benny Blanco himself then confirmed the song through Twitter on 11 July 2018:
https://twitter.com/ItsBennyBlanco/status/1016748701572714497
genius_description.1317:
“I Can’t Get Enough” is a bilingual electronic song by producers Benny Blanco and Tainy with vocals by American singer Selena Gomez and Colombian rapper J Balvin.

Featuring distorted drums and a melody made out of Gomez’ humming, the song features elements of moombahton, as well as Latin and American pop music. The song was released via Blanco’s own record label, Friends Keep Secrets.
genius_description.1318:
“hot girl bummer,” blackbear’s first single since his fifth studio album, ANONYMOUS, was released alongside a low-budget music video directed by Gilbert Trejo, which blackbear and his best friend Cesar Silva creative directed.  This was followed on November 21st, 2019 by a new, higher budget video via Vevo, directed by Adam Powell.

The song is blackbear’s spin on the #hotgirlsummer trend. Megan Thee Stallion fans, who originated the trend, inspiring the song “Hot Girl Summer” reacted negatively to the song, claiming that blackbear appropriated the idea. blackbear, however, claimed the song “has to do [with] the caption trend” and doesn’t parody the song. In fact, he teased the song and title during July 2019, before the release of Megan’s “Hot Girl Summer” on August 9th, 2019.

On the cover art of this playful, energetic track, Maddy Crum, who was previously featured in Aidan Cullen-directed short film, THE ANONYMOUS SAGA, is pictured with a face covered in colorful stickers and a nosebleed. She shared an Instagram story wearing merchandise and another using the official Snapchat filter designed by Harley Wrecks to mimic the cover a few hours before release.



The release date, August 23rd, 2019, marks the one year anniversary of “the 1” and the sixth year anniversary of “N Y L A,” both singles of his.
genius_description.1321:
“Level of Concern” is a “simple but hopeful” song about Tyler’s thoughts concerning the effects the coronavirus made on society and the music industry. In the song, Tyler’s thoughts are presumed to be shared with his wife Jenna as he also asks them for comfort, even if it is a lie.

Inspired to write a song during the pandemic to help the workers in the live music industry, Tyler decided to make his first attempt at writing on an electric guitar. A portion of the single’s proceeds were donated to Crew Nation, an organization that helps individuals who work in the live performance industry who were laid off during the COVID-19 pandemic.

The song’s music video shows Tyler and Josh quarantined in their homes with their families, with Tyler’s then-newborn daughter Rosie appearing in the band’s media for the first time. Tyler and Josh collaborate on the song and video by mailing the USB drive from the single art back and forth to each other.

The popular idiom “dangle a carrot in front of one” comes from the allegory of a mule or a horse being baited with a carrot dangling from a string attached to a stick, which encourages it to move forward. In theory, it should work as means for consistent forward movement for the animal.

Put into the human context, this allegory serves to express J-Hope’s source of motivation in moving forward in his life, career, and altogether in constant artistic growth. Saying “the carrots are on the trophies” points to how awards and achievements (especially ones significant to his career), oftentimes literally trophies, are one out of many motivations he may have in moving forward and flourishing.

The expression of “whipping oneself” is a way to describe how one could be exceptionally hard on themselves, whether it be with full self-discipline or self-motivation to accelerate in completing a certain task. It is much like how a coachman of a carriage uses a whip on the horses upfront to increase or maintain speed.
So basically j-Hope conveys the point that he’s always ‘whipping himself’, or pushing himself forward toward those ‘carrots’ (The trophies which signify success and victory) through several means of hard work, self-enforced discipline and strict practice, which he relates to the word ‘whip’, an instantaneous slash of pain.

It is with these two interconnected metaphors he expresses his solemn, earnest drive to constantly grow as an individual and make progress to walk further down the road.']])]

 Thought I was the one with all the issues', [['According to Genius’s interview with blackbear, he said: “It just talks about toxicity, the song really has this high level of toxicity and it really speaks to me because mental health is a huge deal. For some of us mental health day is every day because it is, and thats the truth.”

https://youtu.be/i9nPI17D4IU']]), ('Medicate myself, different substances, I mix it
 Set my limits, try to draw the line and then she sniffs it', [['G-Eazy plays on the idiom “draw the line,” which means to set boundaries. Although he’s expressing a wish to get clean, his girl draws him into drug abuse, disregarding the limits he set.

G-Eazy often raps about drugs in his music, which he delved deeper into in a 2018 interview with Billboard. Regarding his consumption, he said:

Well, I think that’s a blurry line, it’s not black and white, I think sometimes the line between recreation or just tapping in turns into leaning on or depending on or escaping from.

Gerald used the same idiom on 2014’s “Tumblr Girls”:

Loves the drama, she chose it
She draws the line then she blows it']]), ('See your face on my Explore and then I miss you', [["G-Eazy sees his ex-lover on Instagram’s ‘explore' page, which typically showcases new content. “Missing” can be seen as ignoring someone, but in this context likely means he feels her absence.

Gerald uses social media to illustrate his points in songs such as 2020’s “Had Enough,” where he states:

It’s been this long so why you callin' me?
Texting the homies, you re-followed me

However, this is emphasized more on  “Special Love” released in 2017, where he raps the following:

I know you hate to party, know you want me off that shit
Un-followed you on IG but I can’t lie, I still watch that shit (yeah)"]]), ('Got this magic 8 ball, but I ain’t got no crystal', [['A Magic 8 Ball is a fortune-telling device invented by Albert Carter, according to Magic8ball.org, and uses a 20-sided die that, when shook, provides an answer to a question.

On the other hand, healing crystals are marketed as an alternative medicine and were the subject of a 2017 article by Time:

Crystals or placing them on your body is thought to promote physical, emotional, and spiritual healing. Crystals supposedly do this by positively interacting with your body’s energy field or chakra.

G-Eazy states that while he has the answers, he is seemingly not of sound mind to act on these answers and subsequent advice, and craves the relationship over any stability or progression in his life.

This can also be seen as a double entendre, as “8-ball” and “crystal” are slang terms for cocaine and crystal meth respectively. G-Eazy was arrested for possessing cocaine in 2018.']])]

[('Goin’ live, but we not on the ’Gram', [['“Goin’ live” here seems to refer to a concert or new endeavor. However, Cole explicitly states that he is not referring to going live on Instagram.

Interestingly, Cole has been on Instagram Live only one time. It occurred on January 24, 2019, the day after he released “MIDDLE CHILD.” He joined the Live of his Dreamville signee, Ari Lennox, and the two conversed for about five minutes before Cole logged off.
