[('Acabo de conseguir doble platino sin colaboraciones
 Sólo para mostrarle a un negro que en realidad no lo necesito', [['DaBaby farda del éxito que obtuvo, sin colaboración alguna, su tema “Suge” de marzo de 2019, que alcanzó el octavo puesto en las listas de Billboard y recibió la certificación de doble platino en los Estados Unidos el 16 de julio de 2019.

Cabe resaltar que el álbum debut de DaBaby, Baby on Baby, incluyó colaboraciones de cuatro raperos diferentes, entre ellos Offset y Rich The Kid, pero sus canciones en solitario “Suge” y “Goin Baby” fueron mejor recibidas en las listas que las otras que incluían a artistas invitados.']]), ('Cuando estaba en bancarrota no podía ni comprar cigarrillos', [['En esta línea, Post hace referencia a un fragmento de su canción “Sugar Wraith” del álbum beerbongs & bentleys de 2018.

Fanático de la nicotina, ni siquiera podía comprar un paquete']]), ('Solía tener amigos, ahora tengo enemigos (Uh)
 Solía mantenerlos cerca, ahora están muertos para mí (Maldición)
 Solía tener amigos, ahora tengo enemigos (Uh)
 Enemigos, sí, es muy triste', [['En el coro, Posty canta sobre cómo sus amigos se convirtieron en enemigos cuando se consolidó como una celebridad.

Anteriormente en “all my friends” del álbum i am > i was de 21 Savage, Post cantó líneas similares:

Perdí a todos mis amigos mientras contaba fajos en el Bentley

Es común que los amigos se conviertan en enemigos después de un cambio, especialmente si hay dinero de por medio. Desde que Post comenzó su carrera musical y empezó a generar dinero, se separó de esos viejos o poco confiables amigos que sólo estaban ahí después de los pagos.

En su canción “Paranoid” de su segundo álbum de estudio, beerbongs & bentleys, reiteró esto:

Incluso familiares y amigos comenzaron a cambiar
Desde que recibí ese cheque, los vi cambiando
A veces siento que no tengo amigos']]), ('[Estribillo: Post Malone]', [['La melodía del estribillo hace alusión al éxito de 1984, “Somebody’s Watching Me” de Rockwell, que contaba con la participación de Michael Jackson. Ambas canciones comparten el tema de la paranoia y la desconfianza.  Curiosamente, cuando el álbum Stoney de Post pasó su semana número 77 en el Top 10 de las listas de álbumes R&B/Hip-Hop de Billboard, rompió un récord establecido 34 años atrás por Jackson y su álbum Thriller.']])]
genius_annotations.1021:
[('Y no tienes que decir que estoy loca
 Porque sé que nada ha cambiado', [['En su tema “Him & I” a dueto con Halsey, G-Eazy llamó loca a Halsey en forma de broma:

Si alguna vez me atrapa engañándola, ella intentaría cortar mi (Ja, ja, ja)
Loca, pero la amo, nunca podría huir de ella

Esta “locura” a menudo es relacionada con el trastorno bipolar de Halsey. En una entrevista de junio de 2019 para Rolling Stone, Halsey confesó que se encontraba actualmente en una fase maníaca, en la que estaba muy propensa a hacer “mierda loca”.']]), ('Vendí 15 millones de copias de una carta de ruptura', [['Desde el 7 de agosto de 2019, el sencillo “Without Me” lanzado por Halsey en octubre de 2018, cuenta con la certificación de 5 veces platino en los EE. UU. y tiene 15 millones de unidades vendidas a nivel mundial, según el presidente y CEO de Capitol Music Group, Steve Barnett.

En la pista, Halsey dedica líneas a su ex-novio, el rapero G-Eazy, y habla sobre su infidelidad.']]), ('Llegué, me di cuenta, debí haber seguido mi instinto
 Ya no estoy jugando, miré tu teléfono
 Y vis las chicas en tus MDs y las llevé a todas a casa', [['Halsey expresó un sentimiento similar en su canción “Don’t Play” de 2017, donde, curiosamente, también se habla del fin de una relación:

Me estoy moviendo, me están pagando
Estoy en la mía, tengo espacio para lidiar con eso
Estoy avanzando, se está haciendo tarde
Ve a buscar a alguien y encuentra un lugar para lidiar con eso
Sí, ni siquiera lo intentes
No puedes joder mi ambiente
Con vaso doble cuando ando de paseo
Hijo de puta, no juegues conmigo

Después de terminar su inestable relación con G-Eazy, Halsey, en octubre de 2018, lanzó su exitoso sencillo “Without Me”. En una entrevista de junio de 2019 con Rolling Stone, afirmó:

[me] engañó frente a todo el mundo, como mil millones de veces.

Según un artículo de Daily Star de junio de 2018, durante su tiempo juntos, G-Eazy envió varios mensajes sexuales a una mujer desconocida en noviembre de 2017.

El 9 de febrero de 2019, Halsey condujo Saturday Night Live, interpretando una versión con piano de “Without Me”. Durante la presentación, el fondo se iluminó para revelar paredes cubiertas de notas pintadas a mano, algunas de las cuales decían:

Ashley, te engañé
En casa, en Los Ángeles
En Minneapolis
Más lugares que ni siquiera recuerdo

En estas líneas, Halsey alude a su bisexualidad, lo que implica que en lugar de ponerse en contra de las otras mujeres en la situación, unió fuerzas para confrontar a G-Eazy.']]), ('Medio dormido, a lo lejos te escuché llegar
 No sabía que eras tú y saqué la pistola de la caja fuerte (Maldición)', [['Post sufre de paranoia como resultado de su éxito. Por ejemplo, según Forbes, gana más de $500,000 USD por presentación durante sus giras. Su casa fue allanada después de que se mudó, en septiembre de 2018.

Post habló más profundamente de su paranoia en su canción “Paranoid” de abril de 2018:


Nunca sé cuando alguien viene y trata de quitarme la vida
He estado durmiendo con la .45 todas las noches

Dime por qué no puedo estar tranquilo
Me pregunto cuándo vendrán a por mí
Un paranóico hace planes paranóicos
Haré lo que pueda, pero esto está fuera de mis manos
Batallaré hasta encontrar mi paz']])]
genius_annotations.1064:
[('Only love could kill me, God bless', [["Speaking out of the perspective of Daenerys Targaryen, this pretty much shows the power she owns. Daenerys has survived many assassins coming to slay her as she was growing up, walking out of a fire unburnt, being a target of warlocks, leading a war against enraged slavemasters, charging in battle on top of a dragon with hundreds of arrows flying towards her, flying up north and meeting the army of the dead and eventually setting foot in King’s Landing, the garrison of her main enemy. She has survived all of that, and in the end it will be sacrifice by love which ends her.

In comparison with the question of trust, which was mentioned before in this verse, this line clearly says that only the gods decide what happens to you in Westeros, so Daenerys hopes to be treated well by her gods. Throughout the whole series, gods are heavily discussed. The characters all believe in different gods which are split in the old and the new gods. Even though Daenerys never talked about any gods, we presumably discuss R'hllor, the Lord of Light here, because the red god is known for taking sacrifices through fire which could relate to Drogon and Daenerys who burnt King’s Landing in season 8. Also, Daenerys believing in the Lord of Light is supported by the fact that R'hllor was mainly worshipped in Essos, where Daenerys raised. The Lord of Light seems to be the only real god in the series. Supported by the red priests, it is the most discussed god in the series.

The many gods are mentioned in the song “Too Many Gods“, in which A$AP Rocky and Joey Bada$$ are questioning the gods and their use for the people in Westeros."]]), ('How do I know if I let you stay?
 How do I know if we did it your way?
 You wouldn’t take my place
 Put me away, I’d die lookin’ up at your face
 How do I ever know? Who can I trust?', [['In season 8 Daenerys Targaryen learns that Jon Snow is the legitimate son of her elder brother Rhaegar, making him the rightful heir to the throne. She realises that this would invalidate her claim as queen but as she’s grown to love him and consider him a close ally, she tells him they can continue as before as long as he doesn’t spread the news to his family as she believes they’re untrustworthy.

Jon Snow: I owe them the truth.
Daenerys Targaryen: Even if the truth destroys us?
Jon Snow: You are my Queen, nothing will change that.

However, against her wishes, Jon tells his sisters and it reaches Daenerys’s advisors Tyrion and Varys who begin to plot against her. Daenerys views this as betrayal and blames Jon, though still loves him and attempts to keep him loyal to her. After she destroys King’s Landing in a fit of grief fuelled rage, Daenerys prepares to accept her role as Queen of the Seven Kingdoms and one last time reaches out to Jon to ask him to join her. Jon claims she is his queen and kisses her before stabbing her in the stomach as he was persuaded by Tyrion that despite her positive intentions, she’s doing more harm than good.

Daenerys Targaryen: Be with me, build the new world with me. This is our reason… we do it together, we break the wheel together.
Jon Snow: You are my queen. Now and always.

By killing her, Jon validates Daenerys’s concerns about his loyalty but not in the way she feared. Instead of killing her to steal her crown so that he could become king, he did so as he believed she was a danger to Westeros and his family.']]), ('Who’s hotter? Been a monster with a crown', [['In A Dance with Dragons from the A Song of Ice & Fire book series, Daenerys Targaryen (commonly known as the dragon queen) owns three dragons with whom she shares an extremely close bond. After they’re accused of causing destruction she reflects over what kind of a person she is if the beings she holds so close are able of committing such awful acts.

Mother of dragons, Daenerys thought. Mother of monsters. What have I unleashed upon the world? A queen I am, but my throne is made of burned bones, and it rests on quicksand. Without dragons, how could she hope to hold Meereen, much less win back Westeros? I am the blood of the dragon, she thought. If they are monsters, so am I.
- A Dance with Dragons, chapter 11

A more literal interpretation of the line could be that it refers to the Night King, a supernatural being known as a white walker who is able to raise creatures from the dead to act as his zombified army. The horns on his head appear to resemble a crown.']]), ('Lift the mask, they gon’ have to see what they can’t erase', [['In ‘The Winds of Winter’, the season 6 finale of Game of Thrones, Arya Stark disguised herself as a serving girl so that she could get close to Walder Frey – the man responsible for the deaths of her mother and brother. Before killing him she lifts her mask, revealing her true identity and showing him that he wasn’t able to erase House Stark.

Arya Stark: My name is Arya Stark. I want you to know that. The last thing you’re ever going to see is a Stark smiling down at you as you die.

In the first episode of season 7, ‘Dragonstone’, Arya uses Walder’s face as a mask to kill the most important members of House Frey. After poisoning them at a feast, she delivers a speech as Walder revealing that despite their best efforts they failed to make House Stark extinct.

 I thought I left it inside the past-tense', [['Juice WRLD’s popularity has blown up seemingly overnight, as many of his followers love his emo-rap themed “heartbreak music,” which has a similar vibe to artists like Kid Cudi or XXXTENTACION.

[('In the city where the sun don’t set', [['Wordplay is used here. The east is where the sun rises from, but you can, of course, see the sunset on the West of the Eastside. It shows the correlation they tried to convey between the East on a map and the Eastside of their city.

Although Khalid was born in Fort Stewart, Georgia he identifies himself as being from El Paso, Texas. This is likely to be a reference to El Paso since the city’s nickname is ‘Sun City’ due to its hot/dry climate and its beautiful sunsets.

An additional meaning is Khalid alluding to New York City, as New York is commonly known as “the city that never sleeps”. In fact, Halsey’s old stomping grounds were New York City, and the East Side is every Manhattan neighborhood bordering the East Rivery. Perhaps the sun doesn’t set due to the skyscrapers surrounding the narrator’s field of view, and the neon lights that light up the city, even at night.

Lastly, in a metaphorical sense, the fact that the “sun doesn’t set” symbolizes the hope and optimism of this happy time in their relationship. The day feels like it will never end, just like happiness of their relationship.']])]

genius_annotations.1321:
[('Things are starting to get heavy, mm
 I can’t help but think I haven’t felt this way
 Since I asked you to go steady', [['KISS 107.1 Cincinnati tweeted some of the song’s deeper backstory, revealing that much of the song is inspired by Tyler’s relationship with his wife, Jenna, with whom he had just celebrated their five-year wedding anniversary. The radio station shared:

Tyler’s mom inspired him to write a song for their fans in this unprecedented moment in all of our lives. He decided to write about the last time he felt this out of control. This virus has taken such a huge toll on everyone and as a new dad now in lockdown it makes him feel helpless. He chose to turn it into a love song about his wife. He compares this time of little control to that moment when he decided to commit to a life with Jenna & that uneasy feeling of realizing that when you make that kind of a commitment to someone else, you give up a good portion of control. Its no longer all about you, its about us!

Throughout the song, Tyler compares the commitment of a relationship to being in a quarantine together and a “bunker underneath the surface.”']]), ('Panic on the brain, Michael’s gone insane
 Julie starts to make me nervous', [["In an Facebook Live interview with 101WKQX, Tyler shared that he is not calling out a Michael and Julie that he knows, saying:

I guess when I was writing that song I loved the idea of just name dropping two random people because I feel like everyone has a Michael and a Julie in their life that are either thinking they’re experts on what’s going on in the world or experts on your personal relationship. I personally have a friend named Michael but I don’t think I was thinking of him particularly as much as I was just picking two names that I felt applied to what most people would think as annoying people.

The “Michael” Tyler is talking about is the same one fans assumed he was originally calling out. This is Michael Gibson, who was twenty one pilots' tour manager for five years and ended his career with the band in August 2016, just after Blurryface received it 2x multi-platinum certification by the RIAA. Michael made a fake reaction to the supposed namedrop in an IGTV reaction video as well as a an Instagram post calling Tyler insane."]]), ('Need you, tell me
 Need you, tell me', [["Often during times of crises, people lie that things are going to get better when they don’t actually think they will. They just say they will to comfort those around them.

Tyler is presumably asking for comfort from his wife Jenna throughout the song, a theme that was introduced in “Tear in My Heart” and returned in “Smithereens.”

But if I’m feelin'
Someone stepping towards you, can’t describe
Just what I’m feelin'
…
And you know
I got your six…

This shows their working marriage relationship in that they both support and help each other. Jenna often posts about the two of them on Instagram. When their daughter Rosie was born, she wrote to Tyler in a post saying:


tyler,

you’re a thinker, you’re a trooper, you’re a fixer, you’re a looker still at 6am with no sleep. you work so hard. you are the most diligent and supportive person, I’m lucky you’re my person. Rosie and I love you."]]), ('I don’t really care what they would say
 I’m asking you to stay
 In my bunker underneath the surface', [['With the coronavirus came stay-at-home orders from each state to their residents. However, many people objected to this order due to their desire to remain in contact with other people. While this increased their risks for the coronavirus and being arrested, they saw it as a necessary risk in order to spend time with other people.

The bunker Tyler is referring to is most likely his studio space of a basement. It was a dream project of Tyler’s to have his own dedicated space to tinker and write like that, creating a sort of mini-home for him inside his house. The basement was introduced during the leak of “My Blood”. After Warner decided to release the song early due to its virality on YouTube, they allowed Tyler to upload a now-unlisted video with him playing alongside the studio recording in his new space.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BnAJCv7Aibu/

This may also be a reference to the time Tyler asked God to stay and support him in “The Run and Go:”

Don’t wanna give you all my demons
You’ll have to watch me struggle
From several rooms away
But tonight I’ll need you to stay

While still longing for support, Tyler receives it this time from his family in “Level of Concern.”']]), ('’Cause I told you my level of concern
 But you walked by like you never heard', [['Many people grew more concerned about the coronavirus as time went on and it spread. This lead to stay-at-home orders and social distancing guidelines. However, several people ignored these regulations due to their low level of concern both for themselves and those around them.

Initial reports claimed the disease was most intense with infants and elderly people due to the susceptible state of their immune systems. However, that claim has since been denied but still frightens many parents with younger children. The recent birth of his daughter, Rosie Robert Joseph, may have caused Tyler’s level of concern for her well being to rise.

https://www.instagram.com/p/B82Ctp5ArwE/']]), ('Panic on the brain, world has gone insane', [['This song was released during the coronavirus panic so many of the track’s lyrics mirror what was happening in the world at the time. “World has gone insane” likely references the fact that the World Health Organization had recently declared the outbreak of COVID-19 a pandemic. “Panic on the brain” most likely refers to the state of panic that numerous people went to, many of them buying stores out of supplies like toilet paper.

COVID-19, or the coronavirus, is an infectious disease that causes respiratory illness symptoms that are similar to pneumonia. Those suffering from it often experience a cough, fever, or in more serious cases, difficulty breathing. Many citizens all around the world were being encouraged to quarantine themselves in their houses in an attempt to help slow the spread of COVID-19, and with the United States issuing state-wide stay-at-home orders.

genius_comments.1064: ['In this song, I think we’re getting three different perspectives from each of the verses. Abel is singing from Jon’s perspective growing up with the winter wolves etc., SZA is singing from Cersei’s perspective and Travis is singing from the Night King’s perspective.', 'When Abel start singing', 'Travi$ killing the song with the adlibs', 'pray for me vibes, lets gooo abel😤😤xo', '🔥', 'TRAVIS IN FIIIIRE', 'so SZA has her voice back?', 'Shits sound like pray for me 🔥🔥', 'HOW CAN A GAME OF THRONES SONG GO SO HARDDDDDD!!!!!!!!', 'You know its gonna be fire when you see The Weeknd, La Flame & SZA on the same track 🔥🔥🔥', 'abel bring the heat 🔥 SZA And La Flame ? I’m in heaven already 😍', 'The Weeknd fucking did an amazing job at singing from the perspectvie of John Snow, really using book and show references. Really odd that sza and travis did not take the time and afford to use the same form of writing The Weeknd did on this. Sza as Daenerys and Travis the dragons, would of been epic. nevertheless, Weeknd held it down for the fans.', 'How can someone have Abel in a song and not let him have his own verse?', 'this is fire', "It’s clear that The Weeknd’s verse is about Jon Snow, almost certain that Travis’s verse is about the Night King with some other references, but SZA’s verse can be seen as both Cersei and Daenerys. “I went down for the coldest one” can be seen as Daenerys getting together with Jon Snow, who comes from the cold north. “And I know I’ll win ‘cause I played before, yeah” can’t be put on Daenerys though, and can easily be viewed as something Cersei would think since she has been playing the Game for a long time. “I don’t know with whatever you say\nI don’t know if we need it your way” is another line that works well with Cersei’s character, more certainly with the events of season 7 episode 7 in which Cersei is told by Jon and Daenerys about the army of the dead, something she has never encountered before and which she views as maybe truth or maybe a way of luring her armies out of the capital. “You wouldn’t take my place” is yet another line that can only be viewed from Cersei’s perspective since Daenerys is the one on a campaign to take Cersei’s place on the Iron Throne. “Put me away, I die lookin’ up at your face” is in my opinion the most interesting line, since it’s the one that works best for both characters. As a little girl, Cersei was given a prophecy about her by a witch, saying she will have three children, all of which will die, and in the end Cersei will be killed by her brother, which many fans believe will be Jaime in the final season. From Daenerys' perspective, after season 7, there have been more and more fan theories claiming Jon Snow is Azor Ahai, the chosen warrior, who in order to gain the strength required to overthrow the forces of darkness has to pierce the woman he loves with his sword. Jon and Daenerys are now in love and perhaps the bastard of Winterfell will have to stab his beloved Dragon Queen through the heart to save the entire world. “How do I ever know? Who can I trust?” is another line that can be viewed from both the female characters' perspectives as they have both dealt with many traitors and spies throughout their stories. “Feelings of emptiness” is something Cersei feels after the death of all her children, being publicly stripped naked and her lover falling out of love for her. “Only love could kill me, God bless” finishes the line about Azor Ahai, seeing it as Daenerys has survived many assassins coming to slay her as she was growing up, walking out of a fire unburnt, being a target of warlocks, leading a war against enraged slavemasters, charging in battle on top of a dragon with hundreds of arrows flying towards her, flying up north and meeting the army of the dead and eventually setting foot in King’s Landing, the garrison of her main enemy. She has survived all of that, and in the end it will be sacrifice by love which ends her, and the blessing of a god, the Lord of Light. Thanks if you read all this, I wanted to make annotation but I don’t have enough IQ yet.", 'Travis is channeling some Owl Pharoah vibes in the bitch, by far best La Flame verse yet of 2019', 'YES!!! Three of my favorite artists, I already know this will be a piece of cake', 'Amazing 😍 XO', 'One of the best singles of 2019', 'Damn.']
